Historically, Fenton reaction is based on the production of hydroxyl radicals by catalytic decomposition of hydrogen peroxide (H2O2) using a transition metal, mainly Fe2+, as a catalyst (Eq. 1) (Babuponnusami and Muthukumar 2014; Pliego et al. 2015; M. hui Zhang et al. 2019; Oturan et al. 2012; Oliveira et al. 2014).1H2O2aq+Fe2+aq→Fe3+aq+·OHaq+HO-aq\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
